    <warning>
      <p>
        Trigonometric functions are <alert>functions</alert>, and always require an input (an angle). In particular, an expression like
        <me>
          \cos(x) = \dfrac{1}{3}
        </me>
        is appropriate, while
        <me>
          \cos = \dfrac{1}{3}
        </me>
        is <alert>inappropriate</alert>.
      </p>
